quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  76,23,It was We who sent down to you the Koran by gradual revelation
  76,24,"therefore await with patience the judgement of your Lord, and yield to none of them, sinner or blasphemer"
  76,25,Remember the name of your Lord morning and evening
  76,26,"in the night time bow to Him: and praise Him all night long"
  76,27,"Surely the unbelievers love this fleeting life too well, and leave behind them a heavy day of doom"
  76,28,"We created them, and endowed their limbs and joints with strength; but if We please, We can replace them by others like them"
  76,29,"This is indeed an Admonition. Let him that will, take the right path to his Lord"
  76,30,"Yet you cannot will, except by the will of God. God is omniscient and wise"
  76,31,"He admits into His mercy whom He will: and for the wrongdoers He has prepared a woeful punishment"